{"cursor":"16490","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n{|{{Infobox Aircraft Begin |name = DRDO Rustom |image = DRDO Rustom.JPG |caption\n= A model of the DRDO Rustom-H HALE UAV }}{{Infobox Aircraft Type |type = Remote\ncontrolled unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV) |manufacturer = DRDO |designer =  |first flight =\n'Rustom-1:' November 11, 2009 'Rustom-2:' February, 2014 (scheduled)\n|introduction =  |retired =  |status = Rustom-1 MALE UAV\n(Prototype flight testing)  Rustom-H HALE UAV (Under development)  Rustom-\n2 UCAV (Under development) |primary user = Indian Air Force\n|more users = Indian Army, Indian Navy |produced =  |number built =\n|program cost=  |unit cost = |developed from = NAL's\nLCRA (Light Canard Research Aircraft) |variants with their own articles = }}\n|}\n\n'Rustom' (English: Warrior) is a Medium Altitude Long Endurance unmanned combat\nair vehicle (UCAV) being developed by DRDO for the three services, Indian Army,\nIndian Navy and the Indian Air Force of the Indian Armed\nForces. [http://www.drdo.com/dpi/SAsiaDefnStraRev_.pdf Medium Altitude Long\nEndurance UAV Rustom] Rustom is derived from the NAL's LCRA (Light Canard\nResearch Aircraft) developed by a team under the leadership of late Prof. Rustom\nB. Damania in the 1980s. The UAV will have structural changes and a new\nengine. [http://www.acig.org/exclusives/aero/acig_aero05_nal.htm Chapter 9 :\nNAL and Trainers:ACIG] Rustom will replace/supplement the Heron UAVs in\nservice with the Indian armed\nforces. [http://www.hindu.com/2007/08/27/stories/2007082759890400.htm India\njoins select group to develop UCAV technology]\n","linknr":385,"url":"DRDO_Rustom","recorded":1372158260,"links":["/w/index.php?title=DRDO_Rustom&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=DRDO_Rustom&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom